peak of the pollen season, the relative ICERs rise sharply. For example, in the 
scenario where no clinical benefit is present after premature discontinuation of 
immunotherapy, we have ICER = â‚¬74,770 for SCIT vs. ICER = â‚¬152,110 for SLIT.The 
distance between SCIT and SLIT strongly depends on under which model the 
interventions are meta-analyzed.
CONCLUSIONS: Even though there is a considerable evidence that SCIT outperforms 
SLIT, we could not state that both SCIT and SLIT (or only one of these two) can 
be considered cost-effective for ARC, as a reliable threshold value for 
cost-effectiveness set by national regulatory agencies for pharmaceutical 
products is missing. Moreover, the impact of model input parameters uncertainty 
on the reliability of our conclusions needs to be investigated further.

