On closed-form expressions to Gompertz-Makeham life expectancy.

Castellares F(1), PatrÃ­cio SC(1), Lemonte AJ(2), Queiroz BL(3).

Author information:
(1)Departamento de EstatÃ­stica, Universidade Federal de Minas Gerais, Belo 
Horizonte/MG, Brazil.
(2)Departamento de EstatÃ­stica, Universidade Federal do Rio Grande do Norte, 
Natal/RN, Brazil. Electronic address: arturlemonte@gmail.com.
(3)Departamento de Demografia, Universidade Federal de Minas Gerais, Belo 
Horizonte/MG, Brazil.

Missov and Lenart (2013) derived closed-form solutions to the life expectancy 
and remaining life expectancy at age x when the mortality is governed by a 
Gompertz-Makeham hazard, which is a parametric model commonly applied to human 
mortality data at adult and old ages. However, the closed-form expressions 
provided by these authors are not correct. We provide, therefore, valid and 
correct expressions using elementary calculus. We also consider numerical 
studies using real data to show that the formulas we provide deliver 
satisfactory results.

