OBJECTIVES: â€ƒDogs with patella alta reportedly have a shorter extensor mechanism 
than normal dogs. The present study aimed to measure the length of the extensor 
mechanism and to assess the effect of limb position on the quadriceps muscle 
length (QML)/femoral bone length (FL) ratio.
STUDY DESIGN: â€ƒThree-dimensional computed tomography images were taken of 12 
Beagle dogs. Each dog underwent computed tomographic imaging 24 times with 
