CI [1.03-3.69] and ORÂ =Â 5.7 95% CI [1.2-26.8]), respectively. The presence of 
more than 3 comorbidities and baseline FAC <3 were associated with a higher risk 
of 30-day mortality (ORÂ =Â 6, 95% CI [1.4-24.7] and ORÂ =Â 4, 95% CI [1.13-14.2]), 
respectively. Dementia has been associated with a higher risk of 30-day and 
1-year mortality (ORÂ =Â 4.6, 95% CI [1.2-16.7]) and ORÂ =Â 5.11, 95% CI [1.6-21]) 
respectively.
CONCLUSION: FAC score, number of comorbidities, dementia and the Charlson 
Comorbidity Index have been shown to be risk factors of mortality in 
centenarians with HF.

