summary (MCS [0.6; 1.6; -â€‰2.8]), SF-36 physical component summary (PCS [0.8; 
1.0; 1.1]). Over 6Â years, 63-82% of patients in each group had improved/stable 
SF-36 MCS and PCS scores. Among patients with thyroid AE onset in yearÂ 3 (peak 
incidence), there were minimal differences between HRQL outcomes before onset 
(yearÂ 2) and after onset (yearÂ 3).
CONCLUSION: Autoimmune thyroid AEs (serious and nonserious) had minimal impact 
on HRQL in alemtuzumab-treated patients. These data may aid therapeutic 
